ie.gmit.ngrams

Interface Countator<T,K extends Entry<T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The objects to be counted
    K - Keep counts of the objects, each one can be assigned a rank
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConcurrentLanguageEntryCountator, LanguageEntryAbstractCountator

    public interface Countator<T,K extends Entry<T>>
    Used for counts objects of type T , the count is store in K. Should be use for counting fast and then be able to access the object in constant time, they also have a rank for keep them in a order.
    Author:
    Jose I. Retamal
